ationSubordination in its various forms, principally modification of nouns and verbs, involves tonal marking in some but not all cases. The regular form of modification is that the modifier precedes the modified.. AdverbsAdverbs of time and place are tonally marked. “Adverb of place” includes examples where a place-word (PW) ends in directional suffix (lai6, teng3, kha1, etc.)..	siaN3-mih7 si2-kan# beh7-khi5ggg more examplesSimilarly, there is a sandhi boundary at the end of the duration-phrase in a sentence of the form “have not V-ed in [length of time].” Form: [duration]# bo2-V. Examples: .	chit8-ni2# bo2-lai2.	chin1-ku3# bo2-V.	saN1-ni2-lai6# e6 koh7-khi3=chit=paiCoverb phrases (consisting of a coverb and its object) function adverbially and are tonally marked, except when a pronoun is the object, in which case it is unmarked. .	goa3	kah7 peng2-iu3#	tih7		kong3-oe6 [note ]	Pron	Cov-O#				Part		VO	I		with friends			[progr]	talking	“I’m talking to my friends.”.	i1		ka6 tai6-chi5# 	kong3		hoa6 thiaN1	[note ]	Pron	Cov-O#			V			Compl	S/he	re. the matter	speaks	for me to hear	“S/he tells me about the matter.”.	ka6 goan2-liau6# 	khng5#=jip=khi	[note ]	Cov-O#				V#-Compl	re. materials			put inside	“[Someone] puts the materials inside.”.	iong6 ki1-khi5# 	chiat7-seng3 jin2-lek8	Cov-O#				V				O	by machine			save			labor	“to save labor by means of machinery”.	ti6 chhi6-tiuN2# 	siau1-loo6#	chin1	ho3	Cov-O#				S#				Adj	on the market		saleability	good	“It sells well on the market.”.	hak8-hau6# 	li6 goan3-tau1#				bo2	hiah7	huiN6	S#				Cov-O#						NEG	Adv	Adj	school		distant from “our” home	not		so		far	“School is not so far from my house.”Most adverbs other than time and place, that is those describing manner, do not have a sandhi boundary. Tone change ordinarily occurs at the end of them: .	hiam3+a	‘almost, very nearly’.	tu3-tu3	‘just now’ (also tu3-tu3+a) ggg why not TW?.	poo6-poo6	‘continually, over and over’.	uiN1+